    <title>Real Numbers</title>
    <introduction xml:id="auto_h4zgv689">
        <p component="resources">
            <axiom>
                <xi:include href="../../../source/resources-blurb-sec.ptx" />
                <p>
                    <url href="https://ecampus.idems.international/course/view.php?id=571"> Click here to access the Real Numbers course </url>. 
                </p>
            </axiom>
        </p>
         <p xml:id="auto_fiqf5eig">
        Real numbers represented as <m>\mathbb{R}</m> are a set of numbers that include all rational and irrational numbers. They can be positive, negative, or zero, and can be represented on the number line.
        The table below shows classification of real numbers with examples.
    </p>
    
        
    
    <tabular left="medium" top="medium">
        <row header="yes">
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium">Category</cell>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium">Examples</cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium" >Whole numbers (<m>\,\mathbb{W}</m>)</cell>
            <cell bottom="medium" right="medium"><m>0, 1, 2,3,4,...</m> </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium">Integers(<m>\,\mathbb{Z}</m>)</cell>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium"><m>-4,-3,-2,0,1,2,...</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium">Fractions</cell>
            <cell bottom="medium" right="medium"><m>\frac{1}{2}, \frac{2}{3}, \frac{1}{3},\frac{5}{4},\frac{12}{6},...</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium">Decimals</cell>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium"><m>0.2,4.5,-2.6,-3.8,...</m></cell>

        </row>
        <row>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium">Irrational numbers</cell>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium"><m>\sqrt{2},\sqrt{7}, \pi,...</m> </cell>
        </row>
    </tabular>
    <!-- <image source="Real_Number_Classification.png">
